The paper proposes a new algorithm for constructing similarity graphs using reinforcement learning, which is a popular technique in machine learning and falls under the category of "deep learning" (cs.LG). The paper also focuses on the nearest neighbor search problem, which is a common problem in information retrieval (cs.IR) and computer vision (cs.CV). Additionally, the paper discusses the structural properties of the learned graphs, which is related to graph theory and algorithms (cs.DS). Finally, the paper proposes a probabilistic model for the similarity graph, which is a common technique in artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
